<scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
<head>Scope and Content
</head>
<p>The Archives Vertical File collection contains a variety of research material including newspaper clippings, genealogies, obituaries, copies of publications, research notes, and biographies. In general, the types of items one might find are loose papers, pedigree charts, newspaper clippings, and items that are not suitable for shelving. The collection is arranged alphabetically by folder title.
</p>

<p>Also contained in the files are family histories which may not have been widely published. Incomplete genealogies are included for the following families: Campbell, Davis, Draper, Griffin, Guthrie, Hamilton, Harbin, Harwood, Hatcher, Henderson, Johnstone, Klein, Petty, Reeves, Reneau, Van Buren, and Vaughan.</p>
</scopecontent>

